    "summary": "I offer my:\n\nExperience: I worked for 20 years in Information technology as a senior manager (worldwide responsibilities, division manager in Denmark, CEO of JV in South Africa). Mainly integration and carve outs of Units, Divisions, and other parts. We always came out profitable without trouble. I worked also as a risk manager and business owner. Assignments at Atos size up to 600 staff, worldwide. I have great experience negotiating with work counsils and unions. Some 20 companies, often multinationals, were my customers. \nBefore, I worked for 20 years in scientific and technical research: 10 years as a scientist and 10 years as a manager inside Philips Research (Natlab).\n\nEducation: I have a master degree in Business Management (drs.) and in Applied Mathematics (ir.).\n\nAspirations: Now I look for assignments (part time consultancy and/or as a supervisor) in professional, enterprises, which have socal importance. Think about hospitals, research enterprises, ICT, educational institutions... Size is not important.\n\nAttitude: As a supervisor I believe in dialogue and trust in stead of control. I have 20 years of experience in all kinds of transitions, insourcing, transformation and can easily contribute to manage disruption. \n\nCompetences: analytical (mathematician). decision making (board level management) and creative (scientific research).\n\nMotivation: I think that the transformation of society is the largest challenge and opportunity ever!!!\n\nFinally, I am a member of the Ooa (Orde van organisatiekundigen en -adviseurs), a Dutch society of recognized organizational specialists and advisors. I also finished a course on supervisory boards and I am a member of NVTZ.",
